					<head>Biblical commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420  lccn.loc.gov/n87871045" rend="visible">
						<summary>The commentary of Abraham ibn Ezra on the Pentateuch.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he">Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n79066420   lccn.loc.gov/n82271898">
							<locus from="1r" to="184v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush ha-Torah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש התורה</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/90633023">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88961846" xml:lang="en">Ibn Ezra, Abraham ben Meïr</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88961846" xml:lang="he">אבן עזרא, אברהם בן מאיר</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains a standard introduction and a longer recension of the commentary on Exodus.</p>
							</note>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">אני<name type="person" role="scribe">שם טוב בר' שמואל ברוך</name> ז"ל כתבתי זה הפירוש של ר' אברהם אבן עזרא זצ"ל ליקר השלם <name type="person" role="patron">ר' שלמה ידידי' יזיי"א בכמ"ר מתתי'</name> זלה"ה ה' ברחמיו יזכהו להגות בו ובכל ספרי הקדש הוא וזרעו וזרע זרעו עד סוף כל הדורות אמן ואמן. והשלמתיו בחדש זיו שנת חמשת אלפים ומאה וששים ואחד לפרט היצירה . וסימניך טוב לי תורת פיך "מאלפי" זהב וכסף. לא ימוש ספר התורה הזה מפיך והגית בו יומם ולילה למען תשמור לעשות ככל הכתוב בו כי אז תצליח את דרכיך ואז תשכיל. חזק ואמץ אל תערוץ ואל תחת כי עמך ה' אלהיך בכל אשר תלך. ויוסיפו לך שנות חיים.<locus n="184v"/>
							</colophon>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Friedlander_1967" type="page">63-78</ref>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="1r" to="36v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Genesis </title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="36v" to="117r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Exodus</title>
								<note>
									<p>
										<locus n="111r"/>contains a small piece of Ibn Ezra on Lev. 23:15.</p>
									<p>
										<locus n="111v"/>has an explanation of 1Chron. 29:11.</p>
									<p>
										<locus n="112v"/>contains a commentary of Ibn Ezra on Ex. 3:15.</p>
								</note>
								<quote xml:lang="he">ככה העתקתי ממכתב החכם כי שפתיו ישמרו דעת.<locus n="111v"/>
								</quote>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="117r" to="140r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Leviticus</title>
								<note>
									<p>Following this part of the commentary there is a note on Hebrew measures.</p>
								</note>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="140r" to="161r"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Numbers</title>
							</msItem>
							<msItem rend="v">
								<locus from="161r" to="184v"/>
								<title xml:lang="en">Deuteronomy</title>
							</msItem>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent rend="visible">184 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>344</height>
										<width>240</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>215</height>
										<width>143</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>184 folios (+ 1 unfoliated paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>19 quires: i8, ii-xviii10, xix6. </p>
									<p>Quires marked with catchwords on the last page and signed with Hebrew letters on the first and last pages.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Several mutilated folios.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="30" writtenLines="30">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Pricking and hard-point ruling are visible. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi semi-cursive script, unpunctuated, of the early 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shem Ṭov ben Shemu᾿el Barukh</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, together with <name type="person" role="patron">Shelomoh Yedidyah ben Matatyah</name>, with a date of <date calendar="Hebrew">5161</date> (<date calendar="Gregorian">1401</date>), folio 184v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folios 17v, 23r have censor's erasures.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Luigi da Bologna</name>, a converted Jew working for the Inquisition as a censor (fl. 1590 -  1609): inscribed with his name: Revisto per mi Fra Luigi del ordine de Sa' Domenico setembr del (15)91 (folio 184v). See <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">104</ref>.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Giovanni Domenico Carretto</name>, Italian censor (fl. 1600-1624): inscribed with his name, <date calendar="Gregorian">1618 </date> (folio 183v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">100-101</ref>. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Ivory leather binding. Boxed..</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
